Title: Background Fields in 2+1 Topological Gravity

Authors: A. Toon

Comments: 10 pages, LaTeX, OUTP-93-03P

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D48 (1993) 3720-3724

The partition function of 2+1 Chern-Simons Witten topological gravity has anattractive interpretation in terms of the unbroken and broken phases ofgravity. We make this physical interpretation manifest using the backgroundfield method.